#Qingdao has a lot of well-preserved German and Japanese colonial architecture (1898-1922), but this cathedral was actually built by the German after the city returned to Chinese rule in the 1930s. #explorechinawithcvz

The Jiaozhou Bay region in northwest China was once a German colony from 1898 to 1914 and #Qingdao was developed as the capital of the region. Though the German colonial history only lasted for 15 years (it was later occupied by the Empire of Japan until 1922), many buildings were constructed, and quite a lot of them are still here today. #explorechinawithcvz

Santa Cruz is formerly the Jewish Quarter of #Seville, and it is full of lovely alleys like this.
•
#西維爾 的聖十字區曾為市內的猶太區，在這邊可以找到很多七彩繽紛的小巷。
•
#explorespainwithcvz

#Seville has a lot of beautiful buildings. The bell tower of Seville Cathedeal at the back is formerly the minaret of a mosque that once stood there. The mosque was converted into a cathedral after the Spanish reconquered the city in 1248. In the 15th century, a new cathedral was built, and it remains the largest Gothic church in the world.
•
#西維爾 市內有很多華麗的建築。照片後方的塔樓為西維爾大教堂的鐘樓，由舊清真寺的叫拜樓改建而成。大教堂的原址曾為清真寺，一二八四年，西班牙人在北非摩爾人手中奪回西維爾後，將清真寺改作市內的大教堂。舊清真寺的建築於十五世紀被拆毀，新的大教堂隨之建成，至今仍是全世界最大的歌德式教堂。
•
#explorespainwithcvz

The Iberia Peninsula was ruled by North African Muslims from the 8th to around 15th century. The Moorish influence can still be seen in Southern cities like #Seville today. It is definitely an interesting area to visit!
•
伊比利亞半島的西班牙及葡萄牙，曾於八至十五世紀期間被北非穆斯林統治，摩爾人在半島的南部的影響仍然隨處可見。西班牙南部的 #西維爾 與早前到訪過的巴塞隆拿相比，感覺真的很不一樣！
•
#explorespainwithcvz

Fener and Balat in #Istanbul are formerly the Greek and Jewish neighbourhood. Many of the buildings are constructed along the hill. The setting kind of reminds me of the old Sheung Wan. 😆
•
#伊斯坦堡 的Fener和Balat區曾分別為希臘人和猶太人聚居的地方，不過大部分原本的社群已經離開。區內建築沿著陡峭的山坡而建，有種舊上環的味道。
•
#exploreturkeywithcvz

#Istanbul has a fascinating history. Before it was conquered by the Islamic Ottoman Empire in 1453, it had been the capital of the Eastern Roman Empire for over 1000 years. There are traces of the past all over the city. I’ll definitely come back someday and learn more about this unique city. 😆
•
#伊斯坦堡 的歷史很悠久，曾為東羅馬帝國首都，當時名為君士坦丁堡，中世紀時期一度成為全球最大城市，期後於一四五三年被信奉回教的土耳其人佔領，慢慢演變成為今天的伊斯坦堡，現在在市內還有不少幾千年來人們留下的痕跡。

If you visit Northern Taiwan, I highly recommend you to visit some former port towns along Tamsui River, like #Daxi, Sanxia and Dadaocheng and Wanhua in Taipei. These towns were where business transaction used to be held in the late-19th century and surprisingly, you can still see many of the old western-influenced buildings, mainly constructed during the Japanese colonial period.  #exploretaiwanwithcvz

Isn’t it crazy that these are the buildings that my grandpa used to see when he was young... The biggest difference between #Singapore and Hong Kong is that there are less hills and mountains, which means people don’t have to tear down old houses to make space for higher-rise buildings. #exploresingaporewithcvz

Imagine the present-day Central still has a lot of classical buildings, and Queen’s Road Central is still filled with pre-war shophouses. That’s what you would see in #Singapore. Singapore is very special because of the presence of the past. I wish Hong Kong still had those old buildings. #exploresingaporewithcvz

Before the 50s, much of Hong Kong was not yet urbanized except Hong Kong Island, the Kowloon Peninsula and part of the new Kowloon (Sham Shui Po). New towns were later created to relocate the overcrowded population. #KwunTong was the first 'new town'. A typical 'new town' created back then usually have both a residential and industrial area and an area defined as 'Town Centre', which you can still hear that in bus announcements.

Sri Lanka has a Portuguese, Dutch and British colonial history. Back in the early 16th century, the Portuguese found a walled city in #Colombo. Most of the remaining European-style buildings in Fort, the former fortified town, date back to the British colonial era (1802-1948). This city is full of history and I'm happy to see that old buildings are getting renovated. I'm sure I'll be back to explore this country someday! #exploresrilankawithcvz

node.text: What I love the most about traveling is that it gets me searching for what has shaped the things we see in a place today, and it's even better if I could learn it from locals. #osaka #explorejapanwithcvz

Remnant of the old #Osaka. Though the number of surviving old wooden houses in #Nakazakicho is not as large as Kyoto, which was spared from WWII bombing, it is still a really lovely area to stroll around in central Osaka. #explorejapanwithcvz

I'm quite impressed by the Korea Town in #Osaka. During the Japanese colonial era and Korean war, some Korean moved to Japan. The Korean community in Osaka, a boomtown in the early 20th century, is still very huge today, and you can find everything, from kimchi to K-Pop products, in #Tsuruhashi. #explorejapanwithcvz
Look for the old Osaka in the modern-looking #Kitahama area. #explorejapanwithcvz
Do you know back in the 1930s, #Osaka was the largest city in Japan? #explorejapanwithcvz

Have you really seen how charming #Munich is? I had a few hours to stroll around the city on my own yesterday, and there are just too many architectural masterpiece. 🏛🇩🇪 P.S. I'm currently on the plane.😅 #exploregermanywithcvz
